  <section class="content">
    <p>In diverse societies, multicultural conflicts require a comprehensive approach. This multi-disciplinary research project contributes to the knowledge on addressing multicultural conflicts at the local level. It uses the theory of procedural fairness to enable sustainable conflict-resolution of diversity issues regarding language, culture and religion.</p>
    <p>The project runs from October 2016 to 2021, and is a collaboration between researchers in the field of human rights law (led by prof. dr. <a href="/eva-brems.html">Eva Brems</a>), social psychology (led by prof. dr. <a href="/alain-van-hiel.html">Alain Van Hiel</a>) and sociology (led by prof. dr. <a href="bart-van-de-putte.html">Bart Van De Putte</a>).</p>
